g time (e.g. <b>40-45 minutes<b> for a 9 in. pan). Fewer apples will be necessary for topping the smaller surface of the cake.","Apples can be replaced with pears (prepared as directed for the apples), plums (halved, stones removed), peaches (halved, stones removed) and prepared as directed for the apples), apricots (halved, stones removed), or any other preferred fruit. The amount of fruit pieces depends on the size of the cake. You need enough to arrange evenly over the surface of the cake.","Brandy can be replaced with rum."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","8 slices"]}